title: Australia-Indonesia defence co-operation restored | SBS News
text:
26 Feb 2017 - 11:57am Australia-Indonesia defence co-operation restored Indonesia President Joko Widodo (left) gestures as he walks with Australian Prime Minister Malcolm Turnbull in Sydney, Sunday, Feb. 26, 2017. (AAP) Prime Minister Malcolm Turnbull and Indonesian President Joko Widodo have addressed media in Sydney. Source: Tweet 
Australia and Indonesia have agreed to restore defence co-operation and training activities following formal talks between Malcolm Turnbull and Joko Widodo. 
The prime minister made the announcement with the visiting Indonesian president in Sydney on Sunday after a bilateral meeting which was also attended by Australian ministers. 
Mr Turnbull also announced that maritime co-operation and ties on the digital economy would also be enhanced between the nations, while sugar tariffs in Indonesia would also be reduced for Australian exporters. Advertisement
